WEBVTT

00:25.159 --> 00:28.362
CAPTIONING MADE POSSIBLE BY
WARNER BROS.

01:26.187 --> 01:28.522
[WHALE CRIES]

02:23.977 --> 02:24.978
HEY, MAX.

02:24.978 --> 02:26.547
HEY, SMILEY.

02:29.583 --> 02:31.118
YOUR MOM'S
LOOKING FOR YOU.

02:31.118 --> 02:32.986
YEAH, WELL, I'M WAITING
FOR MY DAD'S BOAT.

02:32.986 --> 02:34.455
HE RADIOED IN.

02:34.455 --> 02:36.457
THEY'RE STAYING OUT
FOR A FEW MORE DAYS.

02:36.457 --> 02:39.427
NO BIG DEAL.
DID YOU TELL HER?

02:40.328 --> 02:42.263
WHAT WAS I
SUPPOSED TO DO?

02:42.263 --> 02:43.831
I DON'T KNOW.

03:24.805 --> 03:27.107
YOU'RE GETTING
REALLY GOOD AT THAT.

03:27.107 --> 03:29.577
HOLD ON. I HAVE
TO BLOW UP 50 MORE.

03:29.577 --> 03:31.712
TALKED TO YOUR
FATHER TODAY.

03:31.712 --> 03:33.747
I KNOW. HE'S NOT COMING HOME.
BLAH, BLAH, BLAH.

03:33.747 --> 03:35.349
WELL, YOU KNOW
WHAT ELSE HE SAID?

03:35.349 --> 03:38.018
MAYBE YOU COULD GO
WITH HIM NEXT TIME.

03:38.018 --> 03:39.587
WOULD YOU LIKE THAT?

03:39.587 --> 03:40.854
OH, YEAH!

03:40.854 --> 03:44.992
[ROCK MUSIC PLAYS]

04:01.542 --> 04:04.345
* WELL, YOU'RE TALKING
ABOUT, TALKING ABOUT *

04:04.345 --> 04:07.180
* WHOA *

04:07.180 --> 04:08.215
* WHOA, WHOA *

04:08.215 --> 04:09.817
* CHINA GROVE *

04:15.088 --> 04:18.459
[SONG CONTINUES]

04:30.971 --> 04:33.541
HEY, HERE'S YOUR PIZZA.

04:33.541 --> 04:35.175
I DIDN'T ORDER
A PIZZA.

04:35.175 --> 04:37.244
THIS IS THE NOAH, RIGHT?

04:37.244 --> 04:38.412
I GUESS.

04:38.412 --> 04:40.781
THEN YOU ORDERED
A PIZZA. 22.50.

04:40.781 --> 04:41.849
THE PIZZA'S HERE.

04:41.849 --> 04:43.951
I'LL TAKE THAT.

04:43.951 --> 04:45.886
YOU MUST BE DREW,
RIGHT?

04:45.886 --> 04:46.887
WHAT IF I AM?

04:46.887 --> 04:48.556
I'M JESSE. YOU HIRED
ME THROUGH RANDOLPH.

04:48.556 --> 04:50.591
RANDOLPH, YOU'RE
MISSING THE PIZZA.

04:50.591 --> 04:51.859
SO THAT'S YOUR SECRET.

04:51.859 --> 04:54.061
YOU HIRE YOUR CREW
THROUGH THE PIZZA FACTORY.

04:54.061 --> 04:56.730
I'M NOT FROM
THE PIZZA FACTORY.

04:56.730 --> 04:59.032
I'M YOUR NEW
RESEARCH ASSISTANT.

05:00.267 --> 05:01.402
[WHISTLES]

05:01.402 --> 05:02.770
Drew: WHAT DID YOU
SAY YOUR NAME WAS?

05:02.770 --> 05:04.672
JESSE.

05:04.672 --> 05:06.374
ARE YOU SURE
YOUR NAME'S NOT WILLY?

05:06.374 --> 05:08.075
WILLY'S A WHALE.

05:08.075 --> 05:09.142
[MAN LAUGHS]

05:09.142 --> 05:10.511
RANDOLPH,
TELL HER WHO I AM.

05:10.511 --> 05:13.213
I'VE NEVER SEEN THIS KID
BEFORE IN MY LIFE.

05:13.213 --> 05:14.815
GOOD PIZZA.

05:14.815 --> 05:16.550
YOU DIDN'T TELL ME
HE WAS SO YOUNG.

05:16.550 --> 05:18.018
HE'S NOT SO YOUNG.

05:19.353 --> 05:20.388
WAIT A MINUTE!

05:20.388 --> 05:21.422
LISTEN, I'LL DO
ANYTHING.

05:21.422 --> 05:22.823
I MEAN, I'M JUST
HERE TO LEARN.

05:22.823 --> 05:24.024
I'LL DO WHATEVER
YOU TELL ME.

05:24.892 --> 05:27.528
OH, WE'RE GOING TO
GET ALONG JUST FINE, THEN.

05:27.528 --> 05:29.730
WHAT DID YOU SAY
YOUR NAME WAS?

05:30.964 --> 05:32.332
JESSE.

05:32.332 --> 05:36.036
OK, JESSE. HELP ME
GET THIS GEAR DOWN BELOW.

05:37.104 --> 05:38.739
ALL RIGHT.

05:44.712 --> 05:45.846
Drew: THE ORCA POPULATION

05:45.846 --> 05:48.516
HAS DECLINED 10%
IN THE LAST 2 YEARS

05:48.516 --> 05:50.818
AND WE DON'T KNOW WHY.

05:50.818 --> 05:52.319
WE'RE GOING TO TAG
EACH POD OF ORCA

05:52.319 --> 05:53.421
WITH ONE OF THESE.

05:53.421 --> 05:54.788
WE'LL BE ABLE
TO TRACK OUR WHALES

05:54.788 --> 05:57.691
ANYWHERE ON THE PLANET
24 HOURS A DAY.

05:57.691 --> 05:59.326
THEN MAYBE WE'LL
BE ABLE TO FIGURE OUT

05:59.326 --> 06:00.561
WHAT'S HAPPENING TO THEM.

06:00.561 --> 06:02.362
WHAT DO YOU GUYS
THINK IT IS?

06:02.362 --> 06:04.598
COULD BE ENVIRONMENTAL
FACTORS, A VIRUS,

06:04.598 --> 06:06.066
MAYBE EVEN OLD AGE.

06:06.066 --> 06:07.067
MAYBE.

06:09.269 --> 06:10.471
FOR ALL WE KNOW,

06:10.471 --> 06:11.605
IT COULD BE SOMETHING
PERFECTLY NATURAL.

06:11.605 --> 06:14.007
THAT'S WHAT WE'RE
GOING TO FIND OUT.

06:24.351 --> 06:25.919
THERE'S MY SWEETHEART.

06:29.122 --> 06:30.691
HEY!

06:42.703 --> 06:44.071
HEY.

06:44.071 --> 06:44.905
HEY, DAD.

06:44.905 --> 06:47.207
YOU READY
TO CATCH SOME FISH?

06:47.207 --> 06:49.242
YOU BET.

06:49.242 --> 06:50.444
LET'S GET TO BED.

06:50.444 --> 06:52.312
WE'LL LEAVE FIRST THING
IN THE MORNING.

06:52.312 --> 06:54.081
[SIGHS] OK.

07:11.231 --> 07:12.399
HEY, KIDDO.

07:12.399 --> 07:13.701
HI.

07:21.208 --> 07:22.776
HERE YOU GO.

07:27.247 --> 07:28.916
Mother:
THIS IS IT, HUH?

07:28.916 --> 07:30.150
YEP.

07:31.519 --> 07:32.753
SO HAVE FUN.
OK.

07:32.753 --> 07:34.588
BE CAREFUL AND
LISTEN TO YOUR DAD.

07:34.588 --> 07:36.023
ALL RIGHT.

07:38.158 --> 07:41.629
Father: WE WON'T BE TOO LONG.
TAKE CARE OF YOURSELF.

07:41.629 --> 07:43.130
I'LL MISS YOU.

07:43.130 --> 07:44.498
I'LL MISS YOU, TOO.

07:49.503 --> 07:50.771
CAPTAIN.

07:57.277 --> 07:59.412
DON'T LET HIM
SCARE YOU, MAX.

07:59.412 --> 08:00.714
OK.

08:00.714 --> 08:03.016
WHAT ARE YOU GOING TO BE
WHEN YOU GROW UP, KID?

08:04.417 --> 08:05.452
YOUR BOSS.

08:05.452 --> 08:08.756
[MAN LAUGHS]

08:21.368 --> 08:24.071
THAT WAS
MY DAD'S KNIFE.

08:24.071 --> 08:26.874
BE YOURS SOMEDAY.

08:26.874 --> 08:28.141
WHEN?

08:30.611 --> 08:32.780
WHEN YOU'VE EARNED IT.

08:35.916 --> 08:39.419
I WANT YOU TO HAVE IT,
AND YOU WILL...

08:39.419 --> 08:40.453
WHEN YOU'RE READY.

08:40.453 --> 08:42.188
WILL YOU SHOW ME
HOW TO USE IT?

08:46.359 --> 08:48.896
I'LL SHOW YOU
EVERYTHING I KNOW.

08:50.731 --> 08:52.833
Mother: BYE, GUYS!

08:52.833 --> 08:53.901
BYE!

08:53.901 --> 08:54.968
HAVE FUN!

08:55.969 --> 08:57.971
Max: BYE, MOM!

09:42.816 --> 09:46.353
[PLAYS HARMONICA]

09:50.891 --> 09:53.560
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

09:53.560 --> 09:55.195
MAKING A CALL.

09:57.097 --> 10:00.768
[KEYBOARD SOUNDS
LIKE HARMONICA]

10:02.502 --> 10:03.771
WILLY LIKES MY
HARMONICA PLAYING.

10:03.771 --> 10:05.338
WHEN HE HEARS IT,
HE KNOWS IT'S ME.

10:05.338 --> 10:08.341
SO YOU THINK YOU'RE
GOING TO PLAY THAT SOUND

10:08.341 --> 10:09.509
OVER THE HYDROPHONE...

10:09.509 --> 10:12.012
AND HE'S JUST GOING
TO COME RUNNING...

10:12.012 --> 10:13.613
UH-HUH.
FROM MILES AWAY.

10:13.613 --> 10:14.614
YEAH.

10:14.614 --> 10:16.349
OK.

10:16.349 --> 10:17.985
[BEEP BEEP]

10:17.985 --> 10:19.286
I'M CHANGING
THE HARMONICA SOUND

10:19.286 --> 10:21.088
TO FIT WILLY'S EAR.

10:21.088 --> 10:22.990
HE HAS MUCH BETTER HEARING
THAN WE DO AND CAN HEAR...

10:22.990 --> 10:24.491
MUCH HIGHER SOUNDS
LIKE A DOG.

10:24.491 --> 10:26.259
YES, I KNOW.
I WENT TO SCHOOL.

10:27.728 --> 10:28.962
I'M PITCHING THE SOUND
SO HIGH

10:28.962 --> 10:30.698
THAT WE CAN'T
HEAR IT, BUT HE CAN.

10:30.698 --> 10:34.134
THEN WE CAN MAKE IT
AS LOUD AS WE WANT.

10:34.134 --> 10:35.836
IF WILLY'S IN
A 30-MILE RADIUS,

10:35.836 --> 10:37.938
HE'LL BE ABLE
TO HEAR US.

10:39.239 --> 10:40.974
[STATIC]

10:44.377 --> 10:46.780
SORT OF A WILLY PAGER.

10:46.780 --> 10:48.448
PRETTY COOL, HUH?

10:49.316 --> 10:51.618
YOU THOUGHT THIS UP
ALL BY YOURSELF?

10:51.618 --> 10:52.920
UH-HUH.

10:53.721 --> 10:54.922
HOW OLD ARE YOU?

10:56.289 --> 10:57.390
HOW OLD ARE YOU?

10:58.992 --> 11:02.696
I THINK THAT'S AN AWFULLY
PERSONAL QUESTION.

11:08.235 --> 11:10.103
[WHALE SINGING]

11:11.538 --> 11:13.073
CAN I LISTEN?

11:16.543 --> 11:17.878
HERE.

11:21.148 --> 11:24.151
[WHALE SINGS]

11:37.664 --> 11:41.634
COME ON. 2...3.

11:41.634 --> 11:43.737
I HAVE
REALLY GOOD AIM.

11:43.737 --> 11:45.638
WITH WHAT?

11:45.638 --> 11:47.207
EXTERMINATOR,
ALIEN INVASION,

11:47.207 --> 11:49.109
SEA CREATURE,
WILD WEST, BUG HOUSE.

11:49.109 --> 11:50.878
HE PROBABLY WOULD
BE A GOOD SHOT.

11:50.878 --> 11:52.079
SHARP SHOOTER,

11:52.079 --> 11:53.280
BITE THE BULLET,
FOOD FIGHT.

11:53.280 --> 11:54.982
YOU'RE NOT KIDDING.
THE KID'S BEEN DOING

11:54.982 --> 11:56.549
TARGET PRACTICE
HIS WHOLE LIFE.

11:56.549 --> 11:57.584
GUNS OF DEATH,

11:57.584 --> 11:59.519
BOOGER TOSS,

11:59.519 --> 12:01.721
SKULL CRUSHING
BOOTS OF GLORY,

12:01.721 --> 12:03.023
POOPER-SCOOPER.

12:10.230 --> 12:12.199
[RADIO STATIC]

13:23.170 --> 13:24.271
DAD, LOOK!

13:24.271 --> 13:25.505
I SEE THEM.

13:32.379 --> 13:33.413
HERE WE GO!

13:38.451 --> 13:40.687
MAX, HERE, HOLD THIS.

13:40.687 --> 13:41.788
WHAT DO I DO?

13:41.788 --> 13:43.023
JUST HELP ME RELOAD.

13:43.023 --> 13:44.557
GIVE IT TO ME
WHEN I TELL YOU.

13:44.557 --> 13:45.859
I'M READY.

13:53.266 --> 13:54.267
Man: NOW?

13:54.267 --> 13:55.268
NOT YET.

13:55.268 --> 13:56.904
NOT YET.

14:03.476 --> 14:05.012
[WHALE CRIES]

14:06.046 --> 14:07.915
Man: YOU GOT IT!

14:07.915 --> 14:08.949
PULL AROUND.

14:08.949 --> 14:10.083
WE'LL CUT THE BUOY.

14:10.083 --> 14:12.052
ADJUST TO PORT,
THERE'S ANOTHER ONE.

14:13.954 --> 14:16.223
TAKE UP THE SLACK
ON THAT LINE.

14:17.490 --> 14:19.359
OK, CAST OFF!

14:21.694 --> 14:23.596
EASY!

14:31.771 --> 14:34.007
GET ME
THE SPEAR GUN NOW!

14:36.843 --> 14:38.711
GET THE LINE.

14:38.711 --> 14:41.214
EDDIE,
GET THE HARPOON LINE.

14:52.525 --> 14:53.961
NOW!

14:54.894 --> 14:57.397
[CRIES]

14:57.397 --> 14:58.598
READY.

15:01.701 --> 15:03.470
DAD.

15:04.938 --> 15:06.439
I SEE HIM, MAX.

15:06.439 --> 15:08.075
GOOD WORK. PORT!

15:11.344 --> 15:12.946
STAND BY.

15:17.017 --> 15:19.319
HE'S COMING RIGHT AT US.

15:24.624 --> 15:26.459
HARD STARBOARD!

15:27.594 --> 15:28.595
HOLD ON!

15:28.595 --> 15:31.931
AAH!

15:31.931 --> 15:33.933
Man: MAN OVERBOARD!

15:48.982 --> 15:51.784
Woman: * WILLY *

15:51.784 --> 15:55.655
* WILLY *

15:56.656 --> 15:59.659
* WILLY *

15:59.659 --> 16:03.530
* WILLY *

16:04.531 --> 16:07.600
* WILLY *

16:07.600 --> 16:10.170
* WILLY *

16:10.170 --> 16:16.576
* WILLY *

16:16.576 --> 16:19.146
Father: MAX!

16:19.579 --> 16:21.381
COME ON, SWIM!

16:22.682 --> 16:24.317
COME ON.

16:33.760 --> 16:35.295
SCARED THE CRAP
OUT OF ME.

16:35.295 --> 16:37.764
SORRY.

16:37.764 --> 16:42.001
OK. LET'S GO BELOW AND
GET YOU SOME DRY CLOTHES.

16:42.001 --> 16:43.770
OK.

16:45.004 --> 16:47.074
TAKE CARE OF THE FISH.

16:57.817 --> 16:59.086
Drew: ANY LUCK?

17:00.587 --> 17:02.021
NOT YET.

17:02.021 --> 17:03.890
YOU--YOU WANT
TO TRY THESE?

17:03.890 --> 17:05.492
THEY'RE
A LOT BETTER.

17:06.358 --> 17:09.296
ALL RIGHT.
SURE, THANKS.

17:12.299 --> 17:16.536
OH, YEAH.
THESE ARE BETTER.

17:16.536 --> 17:18.570
THESE ARE GREAT.

17:18.570 --> 17:20.906
OH, YEAH.

17:20.906 --> 17:22.008
SEE ANYTHING?

17:22.008 --> 17:25.044
NO. JUST BIRDS.

17:25.044 --> 17:26.813
THINGS LIKE THAT.
HMM.

17:29.549 --> 17:31.451
OH, IT'S A LITTLE TRADITION
WE HAVE, KID.

17:31.451 --> 17:33.253
IT'S CALLED
A GROUP PHOTOGRAPH.

17:33.253 --> 17:34.787
NOW EVERYBODY
GET IN CLOSE.

17:34.787 --> 17:36.156
[CLICK]

17:36.156 --> 17:38.325
WELCOME ABOARD, KID.

17:41.128 --> 17:45.132
I LIKE IT, JESSE.
BRINGS OUT YOUR EYES.

17:49.302 --> 17:52.405
Man: YOU LOOK
LIKE A RACCOON!

18:07.019 --> 18:09.322
FIRST DAY, MAX, HUH?

18:10.123 --> 18:12.091
CONGRATULATIONS.

18:12.091 --> 18:13.593
I DIDN'T DO
ANYTHING.

18:13.593 --> 18:16.429
WELL, ON THIS BOAT,
WE ALL DO THE WORK,

18:16.429 --> 18:18.165
WE ALL SHARE
THE CREDIT.

18:18.165 --> 18:19.666
Max: OH.

18:20.700 --> 18:21.701
HERE.

18:24.637 --> 18:26.539
THAT'S A TOOTH OF
A SPERM WHALE, MAX.

18:26.539 --> 18:28.541
SOUVENIR OF
OUR LAST TRIP.

18:28.541 --> 18:30.443
YOU'RE ONE OF US NOW,
KIDDO.

18:30.443 --> 18:32.479
Father: WHAT
DO YOU SAY, MAX?

18:35.648 --> 18:37.484
THANKS.

19:02.175 --> 19:04.377
[TIRE SQUEAKS]

19:15.722 --> 19:17.724
[WILLY SINGS]

19:31.571 --> 19:33.540
[SQUEAKING]

19:39.612 --> 19:40.647
OH.

19:58.197 --> 19:59.532
AAH!

20:00.533 --> 20:02.669
AAH!

20:08.675 --> 20:10.577
[WILLY SINGS]

20:17.950 --> 20:19.986
[SINGS]

20:22.088 --> 20:24.257
GO AWAY.

20:26.426 --> 20:30.062
GO ON. LEAVE.
GO OVER THERE.

20:30.062 --> 20:34.000
COME ON. GO ON.
GET OUT OF HERE.

20:34.000 --> 20:34.967
THEY'LL SEE YOU.

20:34.967 --> 20:36.903
THEY'LL KILL YOU.

20:36.903 --> 20:38.938
[SINGS]

20:38.938 --> 20:41.173
GO ON. GET OUT!

20:41.173 --> 20:42.709
GO OVER THERE.

20:46.746 --> 20:48.448
[SINGS]

21:10.169 --> 21:11.170
HI.

21:11.170 --> 21:15.207
HI. DID YOU
HEAR THAT?

21:15.207 --> 21:17.276
WHAT?

21:17.276 --> 21:18.345
LISTEN.

21:18.345 --> 21:19.646
WHAT?

21:21.481 --> 21:24.784
THEY MAKE
THIS SOUND--PHEW!

21:24.784 --> 21:27.119
SOUND OF THEIR BLOWHOLE.
I THOUGHT I HEARD IT.

21:27.119 --> 21:28.254
I DIDN'T HEAR ANYTHING.

21:28.254 --> 21:30.189
GET ME MY SPEAR GUN.

21:30.189 --> 21:32.559
QUIETLY NOW. GO.

21:44.937 --> 21:46.373
HURRY, MAX. I SEE HIM!

21:50.276 --> 21:51.878
OOH!

21:51.878 --> 21:52.979
MAX!

21:57.083 --> 21:59.151
THERE, SEE IT!

21:59.151 --> 22:00.520
SHOOT!

22:00.520 --> 22:03.022
SAY, WHERE IS IT?

22:05.157 --> 22:06.793
DID YOU GET HIM?

22:11.197 --> 22:12.799
DAD?

22:12.799 --> 22:16.135
Man: HE'S GONE.

22:16.135 --> 22:17.336
YOU CUT YOUR SHIN.

22:18.638 --> 22:19.539
OH.

22:19.539 --> 22:21.608
LET'S GET THAT
TAKEN CARE OF.

22:29.416 --> 22:31.250
DO I NEED STITCHES?

22:31.250 --> 22:32.952
I DON'T THINK SO, MAX.

22:34.487 --> 22:35.955
SORRY I SCREWED UP.

22:35.955 --> 22:38.958
OH, YOU'LL BE OK
ONCE YOU GET YOUR FIRST.

22:38.958 --> 22:40.292
MY FIRST?

22:40.292 --> 22:41.528
YOUR FIRST KILL.

22:43.229 --> 22:44.831
THAT'S WHAT MISTAKES
ARE FOR--

22:44.831 --> 22:47.834
TO LEARN.

22:47.834 --> 22:50.437
YOU MIGHT EVEN GET
A LITTLE SCAR HERE

22:50.437 --> 22:52.772
IF YOU'RE LUCKY.

22:52.772 --> 22:54.373
HOW'D YOU KNOW
THE WHALE WAS THERE?

22:54.373 --> 22:55.975
WELL, YOU GET
A SENSE.

22:55.975 --> 22:58.711
YOU'LL GET IT, TOO,
AFTER AWHILE.

22:58.711 --> 23:01.614
NEVER TAKE YOUR EYE
OFF THE BALL, MAX.

23:01.614 --> 23:04.584
IF YOU DO,
THE SEA WILL GET YOU

23:04.584 --> 23:06.886
OR THE WHALE WILL.

23:08.120 --> 23:09.422
THE WHALE WILL?

23:10.990 --> 23:13.893
DON'T YOU WORRY.
WE'LL GET HIM FIRST.

23:13.893 --> 23:15.127
I PROMISE.

23:28.074 --> 23:29.709
Jesse: RANDOLPH?

23:29.709 --> 23:30.843
HUH?

23:32.344 --> 23:34.313
THANKS.

23:34.313 --> 23:35.948
FOR WHAT?

23:35.948 --> 23:39.752
FOR TALKING BEN AND ANNIE
INTO LETTING ME GO.

23:39.752 --> 23:42.622
I PROMISED THEM I'D
KEEP YOU OUT OF TROUBLE.

23:42.622 --> 23:45.291
AND THEY BELIEVED YOU?

23:45.291 --> 23:46.826
[LAUGHS]

24:10.382 --> 24:13.152
WHAT THE HELL IS THAT?

24:13.152 --> 24:15.121
HEY, YOU GOT SOMETHING?

24:16.889 --> 24:18.457
SOMETHING.

24:19.692 --> 24:21.594
I DON'T HEAR ANYTHING.

24:21.594 --> 24:23.696
TAKE A LOOK AT THE GRID.

24:25.898 --> 24:28.635
ARE YOU SURE THIS THING'S
WORKING RIGHT?

24:54.260 --> 24:55.962
[SNORING]

25:03.903 --> 25:05.572
[THUD]

25:15.915 --> 25:19.218
HEY, BOY, WHAT
TOOK YOU SO LONG?

25:23.522 --> 25:25.057
HEY.

25:25.057 --> 25:27.059
[SINGS]

25:29.662 --> 25:30.730
WHAT IS IT?

25:30.730 --> 25:32.932
WHAT'S THE MATTER,
WILLY?

25:39.772 --> 25:41.240
SOMETHING'S HAPPENED.

25:50.282 --> 25:51.584
COME ON, BOY.

25:51.584 --> 25:53.653
COME ON!

25:57.556 --> 25:59.325
SOMETHING'S WRONG
WITH HIM.

25:59.325 --> 26:01.260
[WILLY CRIES]

26:02.128 --> 26:03.630
Man: COME AND TAKE
A LISTEN TO THIS--

26:03.630 --> 26:05.564
A SIGNAL I RECORDED
THE OTHER NIGHT.

26:05.564 --> 26:06.933
I WANTED TO HEAR

26:06.933 --> 26:08.434
WHAT IT WOULD
SOUND LIKE TO US.

26:08.434 --> 26:09.435
I BROUGHT IT DOWN

26:09.435 --> 26:10.469
A COUPLE
HUNDRED OCTAVES.

26:10.469 --> 26:11.537
THIS IS WHAT I GOT.

26:11.537 --> 26:14.674
[SQUEALING]

26:22.448 --> 26:25.484
THAT'S NO ANIMAL
I'VE EVER HEARD.

26:25.484 --> 26:26.753
IT'S NOT AN ANIMAL.

26:26.753 --> 26:27.854
YOU'RE SURE OF THAT?

26:27.854 --> 26:29.656
MMM, IT'S
JUST A LOOP--

26:29.656 --> 26:32.158
PLAYS OVER
AND OVER AGAIN.

26:32.158 --> 26:34.160
A LOOP OF WHAT?

26:39.899 --> 26:41.167
WHAT'S THE MATTER, BOY?

26:42.568 --> 26:43.903
IS THAT A HARPOON?

26:45.705 --> 26:49.776
IT'S A SPEAR
FROM A SPEAR GUN.

26:51.844 --> 26:55.181
[GRINDER BUZZES]

27:14.466 --> 27:16.068
WHAT'S THIS?

27:16.068 --> 27:18.705
THAT'S JUST A TOOL
OF THE TRADE WE USE,

27:18.705 --> 27:20.039
TO KEEP IT AFLOAT
UNTIL YOU'RE READY

27:20.039 --> 27:22.408
TO BRING IT
ON BOARD DOWN HERE.

27:24.476 --> 27:26.979
WHAT HAPPENS OVER HERE?

27:26.979 --> 27:28.715
THAT'S WHERE
WE HARVEST THE MEAT,

27:28.715 --> 27:30.683
THEN WE PACKAGE IT.

27:31.784 --> 27:33.853
AND FREEZE
FOR SHIPPING.

27:33.853 --> 27:34.987
[DOOR SLAMS SHUT]

27:34.987 --> 27:36.455
WHO DO YOU SELL IT TO?

27:36.455 --> 27:39.391
NORWAY,
RUSSIA, JAPAN.

27:39.391 --> 27:43.095
THERE'S A BIG
UNDERGROUND MARKET
FOR WHALE MEAT.

27:43.095 --> 27:45.364
UNDERGROUND?

27:45.364 --> 27:48.768
YOU MEAN ILLEGAL.

27:48.768 --> 27:51.370
IT'S $200 A POUND,
KID.

27:51.370 --> 27:52.338
Father:
THERE YOU ARE.

27:52.338 --> 27:54.373
IT'S A GOOD TIME
TO LEARN THE HARPOON.

28:00.646 --> 28:02.849
MEANS A LOT TO ME, MAX,
YOU BEING HERE.

28:02.849 --> 28:04.416
ME, TOO, DAD.

28:04.416 --> 28:05.985
GET UP TO THE BOW THERE.

28:11.390 --> 28:13.893
[CRIES]

28:20.666 --> 28:23.169
[CRIES]

28:25.104 --> 28:27.840
[SINGS]

28:27.840 --> 28:30.076
WAY TO GO, JESSE.

28:39.786 --> 28:41.453
THANKS.

28:43.890 --> 28:45.224
WHO'S THAT?
WHO?

28:45.224 --> 28:47.559
WITH WILLY. THEY LOOK LIKE
THEY KNOW EACH OTHER.

28:47.559 --> 28:49.028
THAT'S NICKY.

28:49.028 --> 28:50.696
IS THAT A BOY NICKY
OR A GIRL NICKY?

28:50.696 --> 28:53.432
HE'S A GIRL.

28:53.432 --> 28:55.902
ALL RIGHT, WILLY.

28:57.837 --> 28:59.105
COME ON, BOY.

28:59.105 --> 29:00.672
[CLICK]

29:00.672 --> 29:02.474
Drew: LOOKS LIKE
THEY'VE GOT

29:02.474 --> 29:03.843
BETTER THINGS TO DO.

29:03.843 --> 29:06.278
I THINK I CAN
GET THEIR ATTENTION.

29:07.346 --> 29:10.382
NICKY AND I SPENT SOME TIME
TOGETHER IN PUGET SOUND.

29:10.382 --> 29:12.218
WE'RE OLD FRIENDS.

29:13.185 --> 29:15.221
ONE DAY, I DROPPED
MY LUNCH INTO THE WATER,

29:15.221 --> 29:16.288
NICKY ATE IT.

29:55.461 --> 29:58.330
ALSO, SHE LIKES
TO PLAY WITH HER FOOD.

30:04.703 --> 30:06.338
THERE YOU GO.

30:07.406 --> 30:10.109
Randolph: ENOUGH FOOLING AROUND.
COME HERE, GIRL.

30:10.109 --> 30:11.944
Jesse: OK, WILLY,
TAG TIME.

30:24.690 --> 30:27.593
NOW I'LL ALWAYS
BE ABLE TO FIND YOU.

30:34.233 --> 30:36.302
Jesse: WHAT'S
THE MATTER?

30:36.302 --> 30:37.904
I'M NOT SURE.

30:37.904 --> 30:39.438
IS SHE SICK?

30:43.075 --> 30:45.044
Randolph: EITHER NICKY
HAS 2 HEARTS OR--

30:45.044 --> 30:47.113
OR SHE'S GOING
TO HAVE A BABY.

30:48.814 --> 30:51.217
YOU'RE GOING
TO BE A MAMA, GIRL!

30:54.586 --> 30:56.555
ALL RIGHT, WILLY.

31:07.333 --> 31:09.001
[RADIO STATIC]

31:09.001 --> 31:11.003
CAN I BE LOOKOUT?

31:12.704 --> 31:14.240
CAPTAIN'S KID.

31:14.240 --> 31:16.342
YOU CAN DO
WHATEVER YOU WANT.

31:30.589 --> 31:32.758
YOU SEE ANYTHING,
KID?

31:32.758 --> 31:34.793
NOT A THING.

31:34.793 --> 31:36.628
[WHALES SING]

31:47.373 --> 31:48.374
KUJIRA!

31:48.374 --> 31:50.109
WHAT'S KUJIRA?

31:50.109 --> 31:51.410
SOUND THE HORN.

31:51.410 --> 31:54.913
[HONK]

31:56.548 --> 31:57.916
YOU READY, MAX?

31:57.916 --> 31:59.151
OK.

31:59.151 --> 32:01.187
LET'S GO FISHING.

32:16.002 --> 32:17.569
I'VE GOT THE SPEAR.

32:34.153 --> 32:35.554
Father: AIM RIGHT THROUGH
THE CROSS HAIRS

32:35.554 --> 32:37.023
DOWN THE END OF
THE CANNON BARREL.

32:37.023 --> 32:38.124
LIKE THIS?

32:38.124 --> 32:39.158
REMEMBER, AIM

32:39.158 --> 32:40.759
WHERE THE TARGET'S
GOING TO BE,

32:40.759 --> 32:41.960
NOT WHERE IT'S AT,
MAX.

32:41.960 --> 32:43.029
IF YOU AIM AT
THE TARGET,

32:43.029 --> 32:45.197
YOU'RE GUARANTEED
TO MISS.

32:47.733 --> 32:49.001
READY?

32:49.835 --> 32:51.603
WAIT.

32:51.603 --> 32:53.439
WAIT.

32:53.439 --> 32:54.840
NO!

32:54.840 --> 32:56.108
HAND ME
THE NEXT ONE.

32:58.010 --> 32:59.278
I GOT IT.

32:59.278 --> 33:02.281
Father: NO, MAX.
LET SANDERSON DO IT.

33:04.416 --> 33:05.951
KEEP STILL!
KEEP STILL!

33:05.951 --> 33:07.019
HURRY UP!

33:07.019 --> 33:08.687
DON'T MOVE.
DROP IT!

33:08.687 --> 33:10.022
JUST GIVE IT TO ME.

33:10.022 --> 33:12.324
STEP ASIDE!

33:28.107 --> 33:30.176
DAD, A SHIP!

33:39.017 --> 33:40.752
CAPTAIN!

33:50.262 --> 33:52.498
GET BELOW, KID.
MOVE, MOVE!

33:53.799 --> 33:56.368
COME ON. PICK IT UP!

34:04.810 --> 34:08.179
Jesse: IS THAT
A WHALING SHIP?

34:08.179 --> 34:10.716
NO HARPOON.

34:42.013 --> 34:43.248
THAT'S THEM,
RANDOLPH.

34:43.248 --> 34:44.750
THAT'S GOT
TO BE THEM.

34:44.750 --> 34:47.585
WILLY WOULDN'T DO THAT
UNLESS IT WAS THEM.

35:10.041 --> 35:11.109
YOU HAVE TO CALL THIS IN.

35:11.109 --> 35:12.478
KID, THERE'S NOTHING
TO CALL IN.

35:12.478 --> 35:14.613
YOU SAW IT YOURSELF.
WILLY WENT AFTER THAT BOAT.

35:14.613 --> 35:16.882
HE WAS DEFENDING HIMSELF.
THEY ATTACKED HIM.

35:16.882 --> 35:17.949
AND YOU KNOW THAT
FOR A FACT?

35:17.949 --> 35:19.084
Jesse:
IT'S OBVIOUS.

35:19.084 --> 35:21.153
IF YOU'D OPEN UP
YOUR EYES...

35:21.153 --> 35:22.821
SIR.

35:22.821 --> 35:24.656
BOTANY BAY CHECKS OUT.

35:24.656 --> 35:26.225
IT'S A REGISTERED
SALMON BOAT.

35:26.225 --> 35:28.126
ITS CAPTAIN,
JOHN WESLEY,

35:28.126 --> 35:30.028
IS LICENSED, AND
HIS RECORD IS CLEAN.

35:30.028 --> 35:32.130
YOU'RE RIGHT.
IF THEY WERE WHALERS,

35:32.130 --> 35:33.432
THEY'D HAVE A BIG
NEON SIGN SAYING,

35:33.432 --> 35:34.733
"ARREST ME,
I KILL WHALES." HELLO?

35:34.733 --> 35:36.635
DO YOU REALLY EXPECT ME
TO CALL MARINE PATROL

35:36.635 --> 35:38.370
AND TELL THEM
THAT A WHALE TOLD US

35:38.370 --> 35:39.838
THERE ARE WHALERS OUT HERE?

35:39.838 --> 35:42.073
YOU COULD HEAR THEIR LAUGHTER
WITHOUT USING YOUR RADIO.

35:42.073 --> 35:44.109
STEVENS,
SET COURSE FOR PORT.

35:44.109 --> 35:45.177
YES, SIR.

35:45.177 --> 35:46.545
I DON'T BELIEVE THIS.

35:46.545 --> 35:47.479
THEY'RE WHALE KILLERS,
AND YOU'RE LETTING THEM GO.

35:47.479 --> 35:48.980
WE'RE DUE
IN PORT,

35:48.980 --> 35:50.148
AND PORT IS WHERE
WE'RE GOING.

35:50.148 --> 35:51.517
Randolph:
WHAT WOULD IT TAKE?

35:51.517 --> 35:52.384
EXCUSE ME?

35:52.384 --> 35:53.585
FOR YOU
TO MAKE THE CALL.

35:53.585 --> 35:56.087
PROOF! YOU SHOW ME
SOME PROOF,

35:56.087 --> 35:57.756
I'LL BE HAPPY
TO CALL IT IN.

36:05.197 --> 36:07.233
Jesse:
THAT GUY'S A JERK.

36:07.233 --> 36:09.968
YOU'RE RIGHT
HE'S A JERK.

36:09.968 --> 36:11.270
YOU JUST
NOTICED THIS?

36:11.270 --> 36:12.971
I THOUGHT YOU WERE
GOING TO TELL ME

36:12.971 --> 36:14.573
HE'S JUST DOING HIS JOB.

36:14.573 --> 36:16.275
WELL, HE IS JUST
DOING HIS JOB.

36:16.275 --> 36:17.709
THE WHALERS ARE JUST
DOING THEIR JOBS.

36:17.709 --> 36:19.010
WE'RE JUST GOING
TO FOLLOW ORDERS

36:19.010 --> 36:20.212
AND DO NOTHING
TO STOP THEM.

36:20.212 --> 36:22.714
IT'S NOT OUR PROBLEM.

36:22.714 --> 36:23.515
YOU KEEP THIS UP,

36:23.515 --> 36:25.951
YOU'RE GOING
TO GET ME FIRED.

36:28.554 --> 36:29.688
IF WE CAN'T
FOLLOW THE WHALES,

36:29.688 --> 36:31.022
MAYBE WE CAN GET THEM
TO FOLLOW US.

36:31.022 --> 36:32.524
THEN WE CAN KEEP
AN EYE ON THEM.

36:32.524 --> 36:35.261
WE CAN'T KEEP AN EYE
ON THEM ALL THE TIME.

36:35.261 --> 36:38.997
TODAY OR NEXT YEAR,

36:38.997 --> 36:40.366
THESE MONSTERS
WILL FIND THEM.

36:40.366 --> 36:44.236
AND WE WON'T BE THERE
TO DO ANYTHING ABOUT IT.

36:46.438 --> 36:48.640
IT'S COMING
FROM THAT BOAT.

36:49.641 --> 36:50.776
WHAT IS?

36:50.776 --> 36:53.279
THAT SOUND THAT DIDN'T
QUITE SOUND LIKE A WHALE.

36:53.279 --> 36:54.313
WHAT THE HELL IS IT?

36:54.313 --> 36:55.747
I CAN TELL YOU THIS--

36:55.747 --> 36:58.650
EVERY TIME WE FIND WHALES,
THAT BOAT'S NOT FAR BEHIND.

36:58.650 --> 37:00.486
AND THERE'S
THAT SIGNAL AGAIN.

37:00.486 --> 37:03.689
THEY PLAY THE SIGNAL,
AND THE WHALES COME.

37:05.657 --> 37:06.925
YOU HAVE IT
ON TAPE, RIGHT?

37:06.925 --> 37:07.859
YES, SIR.

37:07.859 --> 37:09.695
SO WE COULD BROADCAST
THIS OURSELVES

37:09.695 --> 37:11.062
IF WE WANTED TO,
COULDN'T WE?

37:11.062 --> 37:14.333
MM-HMM. WE'D HAVE TO GO
INTO PORT FOR A FEW PARTS.

37:19.738 --> 37:22.674
IF THEY CAN DO IT,
SO CAN WE.

37:22.674 --> 37:24.009
YOU DO WHAT
YOU HAVE TO DO

37:24.009 --> 37:25.110
TO MAKE THAT
THING BROADCAST,

37:25.110 --> 37:27.212
AND WE CAN
MAKE THE WHALES

37:27.212 --> 37:28.747
COME RIGHT TO US.

37:42.160 --> 37:43.562
[SIGHS]

37:47.333 --> 37:49.535
WHAT'S KUJIRA?

37:50.502 --> 37:51.703
WHERE'D YOU
PICK THAT UP?

37:51.703 --> 37:56.475
SANDERSON. THAT'S WHAT
HE CALLED THEM.

37:56.475 --> 37:58.176
IT'S A KIND OF SUSHI.

37:58.176 --> 38:00.346
IT'S A USE
FOR KILLER WHALES, MAX.

38:00.346 --> 38:01.647
WE HARVEST THE MEAT

38:01.647 --> 38:04.783
AND SELL IT
TO THE JAPANESE TO EAT.

38:04.783 --> 38:05.984
OH.

38:07.786 --> 38:09.421
WHAT?

38:09.421 --> 38:10.522
YOU KNOW WHAT
YOUR GRANDFATHER

38:10.522 --> 38:11.757
WOULD SAY
ABOUT THAT?

38:11.757 --> 38:13.091
WHAT?

38:13.091 --> 38:16.027
"IS THAT
GOD'S WORK, SON,

38:16.027 --> 38:19.197
SUSHI FOR
THE JAPANESE?"

38:19.197 --> 38:20.366
I DON'T GET IT.

38:20.366 --> 38:22.100
GOD'S WORK.

38:22.100 --> 38:24.135
THAT'S WHAT DAD SAID
WHALING WAS

38:24.135 --> 38:25.537
BECAUSE FOR HUNDREDS
OF YEARS,

38:25.537 --> 38:26.972
THE WHALES THEY KILLED
MADE OIL

38:26.972 --> 38:30.108
THAT FILLED THE LAMPS
THAT LIT THE WORLD.

38:30.108 --> 38:33.278
WHALERS MADE LIGHT.

38:33.278 --> 38:35.814
IT WAS WORK THAT
MEANT SOMETHING THEN.

38:37.383 --> 38:39.351
WHAT DOES IT MEAN NOW?

38:43.021 --> 38:44.556
IT MEANS YOU
HAVE A RIGHT

38:44.556 --> 38:45.891
TO BE
WHAT YOU ARE...

38:45.891 --> 38:47.359
TO MAKE A LIVING.

38:49.027 --> 38:50.762
THAT'S WHAT IT MEANS.

38:54.099 --> 38:55.934
[HONK HONK]

39:11.583 --> 39:14.453
[KEYBOARD KEYS CLICK]

39:29.901 --> 39:33.004
[HONK]

39:37.943 --> 39:39.478
Man: HANG ON TO IT!

40:05.771 --> 40:07.305
HI. WHAT CAN I GET YOU?

40:07.305 --> 40:09.007
UH, 2 CUPS
OF COFFEE, PLEASE.

40:09.007 --> 40:10.442
SURE.

40:13.512 --> 40:15.847
NO SALE. COASTAL
MARINE PATROL

40:15.847 --> 40:18.517
DOESN'T WANT TO KNOW ABOUT
A POSSIBLE WHALING I.D.

40:18.517 --> 40:19.918
THEY SAY CALL
WHEN YOU HAVE--

40:19.918 --> 40:21.086
PROOF. I KNOW.

40:21.086 --> 40:23.321
WHAT DO THEY
CALL PROOF?

40:23.321 --> 40:24.322
Randolph: SHORT
OF ACTUALLY

40:24.322 --> 40:25.491
CATCHING
THEM RED-HANDED,

40:25.491 --> 40:27.926
I HAVE NO IDEA.

40:27.926 --> 40:29.495
CAN I GET YOU
ANYTHING ELSE?

40:29.495 --> 40:31.262
Randolph: THAT'LL
BE ALL, THANK YOU.

40:31.262 --> 40:33.465
WE HAVE TO GET
ON BOARD.

40:33.465 --> 40:35.734
THEN WE GET THE PROOF
THAT WE NEED.

40:35.734 --> 40:38.036
ON BOARD
THE BOTANY BAY?

40:38.036 --> 40:39.905
A WHALER SHIP

40:39.905 --> 40:41.406
FULL OF WHALES.

40:41.406 --> 40:43.609
ARE YOU CRAZY?

40:43.609 --> 40:46.011
I'M GOING TO CHECK OUT
SOME LOCAL FISH MERCHANTS,

40:46.011 --> 40:47.513
POKE AROUND,

40:47.513 --> 40:49.515
SEE IF I COME UP
WITH ANY HARD EVIDENCE.

40:49.515 --> 40:50.882
MAYBE YOU
HAVEN'T NOTICED--

40:50.882 --> 40:52.618
WE STICK OUT LIKE
SORE THUMBS AROUND HERE.

40:52.618 --> 40:54.486
THAT'S ALMOST AS DANGEROUS
AS SNEAKING ON THEIR BOAT.

40:54.486 --> 40:56.154
THAT'S WHY YOU'RE GOING
BACK TO THE SHIP.

40:56.154 --> 40:58.156
I AM?

40:58.156 --> 40:59.090
I'VE ALREADY ASKED DREW

40:59.090 --> 41:00.158
TO FIND SOMETHING
TO KEEP YOU BUSY.

41:00.158 --> 41:01.059
RANDOLPH, BUT--

41:01.059 --> 41:03.495
I PROMISED BEN
AND ANNIE, REMEMBER?

41:03.495 --> 41:06.231
NOW GET GOING.
DREW'S EXPECTING YOU.

41:48.506 --> 41:50.441
NOPE.

41:50.441 --> 41:53.612
PERFECT. GREAT.

41:57.148 --> 41:58.249
HI.

41:58.249 --> 42:01.286
YOU WORK
ON THE BOAT?

42:01.286 --> 42:04.022
SURE.

42:04.022 --> 42:05.691
WHAT'S YOUR NAME?

42:05.691 --> 42:07.058
MAX. WHAT'S YOURS?

42:08.226 --> 42:09.661
RANDOLPH.

42:09.661 --> 42:12.130
SO WHAT DO YOU WANT?

42:12.998 --> 42:15.366
WELL, I'M LOOKING
FOR WORK.

42:15.366 --> 42:17.703
DOING WHAT?

42:17.703 --> 42:21.907
I'VE DONE HERRING,
MACKEREL, SALMON,

42:21.907 --> 42:24.009
ORCA.

42:24.009 --> 42:25.577
WHAT'S ORCA?

42:25.577 --> 42:28.013
WELL, IT'S
A TYPE OF WHALE.

42:28.013 --> 42:29.547
OH.

42:29.547 --> 42:31.149
I DON'T LIKE THEM,
THOUGH.

42:31.149 --> 42:32.784
THEY STINK.

42:34.586 --> 42:38.456
WELL, UM,
I KIND OF LIKE THEM.

42:38.456 --> 42:40.025
HI, DAD.

42:42.828 --> 42:45.230
WHO'S YOUR FRIEND, MAX?

42:45.230 --> 42:47.398
HIS NAME
IS RANDOLPH.

42:47.398 --> 42:48.834
HOW YOU DOING?

42:48.834 --> 42:51.937
Max: HE'S LOOKING
FOR WORK.

42:51.937 --> 42:53.471
YEAH.

42:53.471 --> 42:55.206
WE'RE ALL CREWED UP.

42:55.206 --> 42:57.676
OK.

42:59.745 --> 43:02.814
WHY DON'T YOU SHOW
YOUR FRIEND OUT, MAX?

43:02.814 --> 43:05.083
HE'S NOT REALLY
MY FRIEND.

43:05.083 --> 43:07.218
I'M GOING TO GO
SEE MOM NOW.

43:07.218 --> 43:08.754
SURE.

43:09.721 --> 43:11.690
SEE YOU AROUND.

43:40.285 --> 43:41.252
HEY!

43:41.252 --> 43:44.189
I SEE YOU GOT EDDIE
WORKING THE HOSE.

43:44.189 --> 43:46.024
HOW YOU DOING?

43:48.927 --> 43:50.195
Father: JUST SIGN
ON THE LINE.

43:52.363 --> 43:53.398
WHAT'S GOING ON?

43:57.769 --> 43:59.204
[BEEP BEEP]

44:00.772 --> 44:01.773
HEY, MAX!

44:01.773 --> 44:02.908
I GOT TO GO.

44:02.908 --> 44:05.076
WHAT'S YOUR DAD
REALLY FISHING FOR?

44:05.076 --> 44:07.545
MY DAD'S
A SALMON BOAT CAPTAIN.

44:07.545 --> 44:09.347
OH.

44:11.416 --> 44:13.118
YEAH, WELL, HE IS.

44:40.178 --> 44:41.713
I LIED TO YOU.

44:41.713 --> 44:44.149
BIG WHOOP.

44:44.149 --> 44:45.717
[SIGHS]

44:47.919 --> 44:49.721
I'M NOT A WHALER.

44:49.721 --> 44:51.622
SO WHAT?

44:51.622 --> 44:54.292
WELL, I'M SORT OF
THE OPPOSITE.

44:54.292 --> 44:55.260
YOU'RE A WHALE?

44:55.260 --> 44:59.664
NO, BUT I'M TRYING
TO PROTECT THEM.

44:59.664 --> 45:01.666
[SIGHS]

45:01.666 --> 45:03.534
WHAT HE'S DOING'S WRONG,
AND YOU KNOW IT.

45:03.534 --> 45:04.669
WHO?

45:04.669 --> 45:05.771
YOUR DAD.

45:05.771 --> 45:08.940
MY DAD'S
A SALMON BOAT CAPTAIN.

45:10.641 --> 45:12.778
WHY DO YOU CARE, ANYWAY?

45:12.778 --> 45:14.780
IF ONE OF YOUR FRIENDS
WAS IN TROUBLE,

45:14.780 --> 45:16.247
WOULDN'T YOU TRY
TO HELP THEM?

45:16.247 --> 45:17.883
IF I COULD.

45:17.883 --> 45:20.952
MY FRIENDS ARE WHALES.

45:23.922 --> 45:26.291
I DON'T KNOW WHAT
YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT.

45:26.291 --> 45:28.093
SURE YOU DO.

45:28.093 --> 45:29.761
[SIGHS]
I'LL SHOW YOU.

45:29.761 --> 45:30.829
WHAT?

45:30.829 --> 45:33.364
THE WHALES.
I'LL INTRODUCE YOU.

45:34.632 --> 45:36.334
WHOA!

45:37.769 --> 45:39.237
COME HERE.

45:42.707 --> 45:44.843
THAT GAMEBOY TELLS YOU
WHERE WHALES ARE?

45:44.843 --> 45:47.512
NOT ALL, JUST ONE.

46:10.668 --> 46:11.769
Jesse: LISTEN.

46:11.769 --> 46:13.471
[WHALES SING]

46:14.806 --> 46:16.041
THEY'RE CLOSE.

46:18.743 --> 46:20.178
[WHALES SING]

46:20.178 --> 46:22.347
IT'S QUITE A SOUND,
ISN'T IT?

46:22.347 --> 46:23.882
YEAH.

46:25.083 --> 46:26.684
DO YOU KNOW AN ORCA
IS MOSTLY WATER?

46:26.684 --> 46:27.819
SURE.

46:27.819 --> 46:30.021
BUT DID YOU KNOW
THAT WHEN HE SINGS,

46:30.021 --> 46:32.991
YOU CAN FEEL
THE BEAT OF HIS SONG

46:32.991 --> 46:35.126
IN TIME
WITH THE WAVES.

46:37.295 --> 46:40.065
[WHALES SING]

46:42.467 --> 46:44.836
WHY DO THEY DO THAT?

46:44.836 --> 46:48.940
I SAY IT'S BECAUSE
THEY'RE GOOD MUSICIANS,

46:48.940 --> 46:51.042
BUT A FRIEND OF MINE
THINKS DIFFERENTLY.

46:51.042 --> 46:54.212
HE SAYS THE WHOLE EARTH
IS BREATHING.

46:54.212 --> 46:58.416
AND THAT THEIR SONG
IS THE EARTH BREATHING.

46:58.416 --> 47:01.953
[BIRD SQUAWKS]

47:25.076 --> 47:26.244
Jesse:
THERE THEY ARE.

47:26.244 --> 47:28.179
CAN I LOOK?
YEAH. HERE.

47:28.179 --> 47:29.180
THANKS.

47:30.515 --> 47:33.885
OH, YEAH.

47:42.493 --> 47:44.930
[SQUEAK]

47:47.698 --> 47:49.901
[WHALES SING]

47:56.975 --> 47:58.944
Max: WHOA!

47:59.744 --> 48:01.312
WHOA!
WHOA!

48:01.312 --> 48:02.313
HEY, BOY.

48:05.750 --> 48:08.086
WHERE'D HE GO?

48:09.587 --> 48:10.922
[SINGING]

48:13.891 --> 48:16.094
HE LIKES TO PLAY GAMES.

48:16.094 --> 48:18.229
WHAT GAMES
DOES HE KNOW?

48:18.229 --> 48:19.864
[THUD]

48:19.864 --> 48:22.700
FETCH. FETCH BY FAR
HIS FAVORITE.

48:22.700 --> 48:24.702
WHAT DOES HE FETCH?

48:24.702 --> 48:26.471
YOU'LL SEE.

50:36.000 --> 50:37.268
Max: WHAT?

50:37.268 --> 50:39.270
I'VE NEVER SEEN HIM

50:39.270 --> 50:41.005
TAKE TO ANYONE
LIKE THAT BEFORE...

50:41.005 --> 50:42.807
EXCEPT ONCE.

50:46.144 --> 50:48.946
I THOUGHT MAYBE HE WAS
LIKE THAT WITH EVERYONE.

50:48.946 --> 50:51.116
NO. HE'S ONLY LIKE
THAT WITH FAMILY.

50:51.116 --> 50:53.151
WELL, I'M NOT HIS FAMILY.

50:53.151 --> 50:54.619
TELL HIM THAT.

50:59.023 --> 51:01.092
IS THIS YOUR JOB?

51:01.092 --> 51:02.427
YEAH.

51:03.928 --> 51:05.496
DO YOU LIKE IT?

51:05.496 --> 51:07.098
OH, YEAH.

51:10.635 --> 51:13.037
I DIDN'T KNOW PEOPLE
HAD JOBS LIKE THAT.

51:13.037 --> 51:15.173
NEITHER DID I.

51:15.173 --> 51:17.242
HEY, TURN IN THERE.

51:34.525 --> 51:36.994
ME AND MY DAD BUILT
THIS PORCH LAST SUMMER.

51:36.994 --> 51:38.429
OH, YEAH?

51:43.968 --> 51:45.170
IT'S A BIG FAMILY.

51:45.170 --> 51:46.471
Max: YEAH.

51:46.471 --> 51:48.973
WHAT'S IT LIKE TO HAVE
A BIG FAMILY LIKE THIS?

51:48.973 --> 51:51.075
OH, JUST LIKE ANY
FAMILY, YOU KNOW?

51:51.075 --> 51:52.577
NO, I DON'T.

51:57.348 --> 51:58.983
THIS ISN'T RIGHT.

51:58.983 --> 52:00.185
WHAT?

52:00.185 --> 52:01.419
EVEN THOUGH HE'S DOING
SOMETHING WRONG,

52:01.419 --> 52:03.688
HE'S STILL YOUR DAD.

52:06.624 --> 52:07.892
YOU DROPPED THIS.

52:07.892 --> 52:10.328
I DON'T WANT IT.

52:12.930 --> 52:14.632
STOP HIM MYSELF.

52:16.834 --> 52:18.436
[DOOR CLOSES]

52:38.122 --> 52:39.657
JESSE?

52:43.961 --> 52:45.496
JESSE?

52:53.904 --> 52:55.740
[STATIC]

52:58.142 --> 52:59.377
JESSE?

52:59.377 --> 53:00.378
[WHISPERING]
Randolph?

53:00.378 --> 53:02.280
WHERE ARE YOU?

53:02.280 --> 53:04.282
I'M GETTING THE PROOF
WE NEED.

53:04.282 --> 53:05.883
WHERE ARE YOU?

53:05.883 --> 53:06.851
IF I TELL YOU,

53:06.851 --> 53:08.253
YOU GOTTA PROMISE
NOT TO BE MAD AT ME.

53:08.253 --> 53:10.054
YOU HAVE ANY IDEA
WHAT THEY'LL DO TO YOU

53:10.054 --> 53:11.289
IF THEY CATCH YOU?

53:11.289 --> 53:12.757
YOU KNOW WHAT THEY'RE
GOING TO DO TO WILLY

53:12.757 --> 53:13.958
IF THEY CATCH HIM?

53:13.958 --> 53:16.427
NOW I'M MORE WORRIED ABOUT YOU
THAN I AM ABOUT WILLY.

53:16.427 --> 53:18.429
LISTEN. WESLEY'S
STILL AT THE BAR.

53:18.429 --> 53:19.830
KEEP HIM THERE.

53:19.830 --> 53:23.033
I DON'T WANT THIS BOAT
LEAVING WITH ME ON IT.

53:23.033 --> 53:24.034
JESSE--

53:24.034 --> 53:25.736
SORRY, GOTTA GO!

53:28.606 --> 53:29.674
JESSE?

53:50.328 --> 53:52.363
[VIDEO GAME BEEPS]

53:53.264 --> 53:54.265
MOM?

53:54.265 --> 53:55.266
YES, MAX.

53:55.266 --> 53:56.667
WHAT DO YOU DO
IF SOMEBODY'S

53:56.667 --> 53:59.537
MAKING YOU DO SOMETHING
THAT YOU DON'T WANT TO?

53:59.537 --> 54:00.338
WHO?

54:00.338 --> 54:01.772
OH, JUST SOMEONE.

54:01.772 --> 54:04.809
YOU SHOULD NEVER LET OTHER
PEOPLE TELL YOU WHAT TO DO.

54:04.809 --> 54:06.477
YOU HAVE TO STICK UP
FOR YOURSELF.

54:06.477 --> 54:08.479
YOU DO WHAT
YOU THINK IS RIGHT.

54:08.479 --> 54:10.080
DO YOU ALWAYS
DO WHAT'S RIGHT,

54:10.080 --> 54:12.082
EVEN IF IT HURTS?

54:12.082 --> 54:13.484
THAT'S THE HARDEST PART.

54:13.484 --> 54:16.086
YOU SHOULD DO IT
EVEN IF IT HURTS.

54:16.086 --> 54:19.056
IS THAT WHAT
YOU DO, MOM?

54:19.056 --> 54:20.458
I TRY MY BEST.

54:20.458 --> 54:21.859
UHH! ALL RIGHT!

54:21.859 --> 54:22.860
BED.

54:22.860 --> 54:23.861
NO.

54:23.861 --> 54:24.729
BED.
NO.

54:24.729 --> 54:28.299
WE'LL TAKE 2
OF THE TALL ONES.

54:33.438 --> 54:35.573
THANKS A LOT.

54:37.408 --> 54:38.943
[MAN LAUGHING]

54:38.943 --> 54:40.545
PUT THAT AWAY.

54:56.727 --> 54:58.929
YOU SHOULD GO GET
THE CAPTAIN.

54:58.929 --> 55:00.331
TAKE YOUR TIME

55:00.331 --> 55:02.132
AND GET A GOOD NIGHT'S
SLEEP TONIGHT.

55:02.132 --> 55:06.337
HE SAYS HE WANTS TO LEAVE
AS SOON AS WE'RE READY.

55:06.337 --> 55:07.938
ALL RIGHT, ALL RIGHT.

55:07.938 --> 55:09.073
OOH!

55:11.742 --> 55:12.743
[CLATTERING]

55:12.743 --> 55:13.544
UHH!

55:13.544 --> 55:15.713
DON'T WORRY.
I'LL GET THOSE.

55:15.713 --> 55:16.714
AAH!

55:20.518 --> 55:22.520
RANDOLPH, I THINK
I FOUND SOMETHING.

55:22.520 --> 55:24.555
JESSE,
GET OUT OF THERE.

55:24.555 --> 55:26.824
I DON'T THINK THEY'RE
GOING TO BE HERE MUCH LONGER.

55:26.824 --> 55:28.826
YOU GOTTA BUY ME
SOME MORE TIME.

55:28.826 --> 55:32.029
Randolph: WHAT DO YOU
EXPECT ME TO DO?

55:32.029 --> 55:33.398
JESSE?

55:33.398 --> 55:34.699
JESSE?

55:34.699 --> 55:36.601
ASK THEM TO DANCE
OR SOMETHING.

55:36.601 --> 55:38.536
THEY'RE NOT MY TYPE.

55:41.071 --> 55:43.408
WISH ME LUCK.

55:43.408 --> 55:44.742
Randolph: GOOD LUCK.

55:48.546 --> 55:50.748
WHAT IF THEY
CATCH HIM?

55:50.748 --> 55:51.749
WHO?

55:51.749 --> 55:53.150
YOUR FATHER?

55:53.150 --> 55:55.486
HE'LL NEVER GET CAUGHT.

55:56.587 --> 55:58.723
WOULD HE HAVE
TO GO TO JAIL?

55:58.723 --> 56:01.726
NO. HONEY, IS THAT
WHAT YOU'RE WORRIED ABOUT?

56:01.726 --> 56:04.194
HE WOULD NEVER
HAVE TO GO TO JAIL.

56:04.194 --> 56:06.597
THEN WHAT WOULD HAPPEN?

56:06.597 --> 56:08.799
THEY'D TAKE AWAY
HIS BOAT,

56:08.799 --> 56:09.600
THAT'S ALL.

56:09.600 --> 56:12.202
MAYBE MAKE HIM
PAY A FINE.

56:12.202 --> 56:13.471
PROMISE?

56:13.471 --> 56:15.806
YEAH, I PROMISE.

56:17.475 --> 56:20.344
YOU KNOW YOUR FATHER
LOVES YOU VERY MUCH,

56:20.344 --> 56:21.345
DON'T YOU?

56:21.345 --> 56:22.480
YEAH.

56:22.480 --> 56:24.148
HE DOES WHAT HE DOES
FOR YOU AND ME,

56:24.148 --> 56:28.352
TO MAKE US HAPPY,
PUT A ROOF OVER OUR HEADS.

56:28.352 --> 56:30.421
YEAH, BUT DON'T YOU
EVER WISH--

56:30.421 --> 56:31.722
NO, MAX, I DON'T.

56:31.722 --> 56:34.324
DON'T YOU EVER WISH
HE WOULD STOP?

56:34.324 --> 56:36.326
DON'T YOU EVER WISH

56:36.326 --> 56:38.529
HE WOULD DO
SOMETHING ELSE?

56:40.230 --> 56:42.399
I LOVE YOU, MAX.

56:44.635 --> 56:46.236
YOU COULD TELL HIM.

56:46.236 --> 56:47.738
HE'D LISTEN TO YOU.

56:47.738 --> 56:50.007
I BELIEVE IN YOUR DAD.

56:50.007 --> 56:53.177
I SUPPORT HIM,
FOR BETTER OR WORSE.

56:53.177 --> 56:54.779
GOOD NIGHT, MAX.

56:57.482 --> 57:01.819
[MUFFLED SHOUTING]

57:06.223 --> 57:07.858
EXCUSE ME, MISS.

57:11.161 --> 57:14.499
OK, GUYS, KRON SAYS HE'S GOT
EVERYTHING WIRED UP,

57:14.499 --> 57:15.900
READY TO GO, SO...

57:15.900 --> 57:17.502
CANCEL OUR ORDER.
LET'S GO.

57:27.044 --> 57:29.446
[FEIGNING DRUNKENNESS]
AH, WESLEY! HA HA HA!

57:29.446 --> 57:30.447
JOHN WESLEY!

57:30.447 --> 57:32.049
I THOUGHT IT WAS YOU.

57:32.049 --> 57:33.417
DO I KNOW YOU?

57:33.417 --> 57:34.752
RANDOLPH.

57:34.752 --> 57:36.954
Randolph: I REMEMBER YOU
FROM THE OLD DAYS.

57:36.954 --> 57:38.388
I HIT THE JACKPOT.

57:38.388 --> 57:39.690
I DON'T THINK
I REMEMBER YOU

57:39.690 --> 57:40.825
FROM THE OLD DAYS.

57:40.825 --> 57:42.827
OH, WELL.
BUT I REMEMBER YOU.

57:42.827 --> 57:45.029
BOY, DO I REMEMBER YOU.

57:45.029 --> 57:47.331
HA HA HA HA HA!

57:47.331 --> 57:49.567
HA HA HA HA HA!

57:49.567 --> 57:52.036
RANDOLPH,
STOP FOOLING AROUND.

57:52.036 --> 57:54.304
HA HA HA HA HA!

57:54.304 --> 57:57.174
[EVERYONE LAUGHING]

57:59.577 --> 58:00.711
WE'RE ON OUR WAY OUT.

58:00.711 --> 58:02.312
WE'LL CATCH YOU UP
NEXT TIME, FRIEND.

58:02.312 --> 58:03.714
YOU DON'T SEEM
TO UNDERSTAND.

58:03.714 --> 58:05.850
I KNOW WHO YOU ARE,
AND I KNOW WHAT YOU DO,

58:05.850 --> 58:07.051
AND I'M NO FRIEND
OF YOURS.

58:15.192 --> 58:16.527
RANDOLPH?

58:17.327 --> 58:18.763
HEY!

58:25.402 --> 58:27.004
[SOUNDS OF FIGHTING]

58:27.004 --> 58:28.238
GREAT.

58:37.514 --> 58:40.517
YOU'RE MAKING A MISTAKE.

58:42.052 --> 58:45.623
I SUGGEST YOU RIDE OUT
ON THE BOAT YOU CAME IN ON.

58:53.898 --> 58:55.299
THANKS.

58:55.299 --> 58:57.101
DON'T MENTION IT.

58:57.101 --> 58:59.704
THE NATIVES DON'T LOOK
TOO FRIENDLY.

58:59.704 --> 59:01.839
YEAH. LET'S GET A DRINK.

59:24.294 --> 59:26.631
[MEN TALKING]

59:26.631 --> 59:28.599
DINEEN, MAKE SOME COFFEE.

59:28.599 --> 59:29.634
OK.

59:29.634 --> 59:31.802
LET'S GET THE HELL
OUT OF HERE.

59:31.802 --> 59:33.037
YOU GOT MY VOTE.

59:33.037 --> 59:34.038
YES, SIR.

59:46.717 --> 59:48.285
[SPEARS CLANK]

59:54.659 --> 59:56.060
READY.

01:00:14.044 --> 01:00:15.713
STANDING BY!

01:00:34.098 --> 01:00:36.266
[ENGINE STARTS]

01:00:53.617 --> 01:00:55.319
STERN'S AWEIGH!

01:01:09.199 --> 01:01:12.069
[ENGINE CLANKING]

01:01:19.409 --> 01:01:21.712
AW, GREAT.

01:01:21.712 --> 01:01:22.747
[CLICK]

01:01:22.747 --> 01:01:23.781
[GASP]

01:01:23.781 --> 01:01:25.182
YOU DROPPED THIS.

01:01:25.182 --> 01:01:28.218
GIVE ME THAT.
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

01:01:28.218 --> 01:01:29.720
GETTING IN TROUBLE.

01:01:31.455 --> 01:01:32.990
[TURNS ENGINE OFF]

01:01:43.734 --> 01:01:45.069
SO WHAT ARE WE
GONNA DO?

01:01:45.069 --> 01:01:47.872
WE'RE GONNA HAVE TO
SWIM BACK TO SHORE.

01:01:47.872 --> 01:01:49.306
WE ARE NOT.

01:01:49.306 --> 01:01:50.307
ALL RIGHT.

01:01:50.307 --> 01:01:51.541
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

01:01:51.541 --> 01:01:53.410
SEE YOU LATER.

01:01:59.249 --> 01:02:00.450
HERE'S YOUR PROOF.

01:02:00.450 --> 01:02:02.486
I PULLED THIS OUT OF
WILLY'S TAIL 2 DAYS AGO.

01:02:02.486 --> 01:02:05.389
THIS I FOUND UNDER THE DECK
OF THE BOTANY BAY.

01:02:05.389 --> 01:02:07.357
Randolph:
WE WERE RIGHT.

01:02:07.357 --> 01:02:09.259
I SEE.

01:02:09.259 --> 01:02:10.227
WE GOTTA STOP THEM.

01:02:10.227 --> 01:02:12.029
THAT'S EXACTLY WHAT
WE'RE GOING TO DO.

01:02:12.029 --> 01:02:14.731
WE'LL CALL THIS IN
FIRST THING IN THE MORNING.

01:02:14.731 --> 01:02:16.767
WE COULD PUT THESE GUYS
OUT OF BUSINESS,

01:02:16.767 --> 01:02:18.335
BUT ONLY IF
WE MOVE RIGHT NOW.

01:02:18.335 --> 01:02:19.236
I'M NOT ABOUT TO RISK

01:02:19.236 --> 01:02:20.771
$2 MILLION
WORTH OF EQUIPMENT

01:02:20.771 --> 01:02:22.706
TO DO
THE MARINE PATROL'S JOB.

01:02:22.706 --> 01:02:24.842
THERE ARE RULES THAT
HAVE TO BE FOLLOWED.

01:02:24.842 --> 01:02:26.944
NOW, WHY DON'T YOU
JUST SIT DOWN,

01:02:26.944 --> 01:02:28.645
AND I'LL GET YOU A SODA.

01:02:28.645 --> 01:02:30.614
WE'VE GOT
A VERY BUSY DAY

01:02:30.614 --> 01:02:31.648
AHEAD OF US TOMORROW.

01:02:31.648 --> 01:02:32.817
NO, THANKS.

01:02:32.817 --> 01:02:33.851
I'M A LITTLE TIRED.

01:02:33.851 --> 01:02:34.819
I'M GOING TO
CATCH SOME SLEEP.

01:02:34.819 --> 01:02:35.820
SUIT YOURSELF.

01:02:35.820 --> 01:02:36.821
GOOD NIGHT.

01:02:36.821 --> 01:02:37.822
GOOD NIGHT.

01:02:37.822 --> 01:02:39.790
THANKS FOR
ALL YOU'VE DONE.

01:02:39.790 --> 01:02:41.391
AH, IT WAS NOTHING.

01:02:41.391 --> 01:02:42.927
NO KIDDING.

01:02:45.495 --> 01:02:47.297
THOSE GUYS
HAVE ALREADY LEFT.

01:02:47.297 --> 01:02:50.500
THEY'RE GOING AFTER
THE WHOLE POD TONIGHT--

01:02:50.500 --> 01:02:52.803
WILLY, NICKY,
NICKY'S BABY.

01:02:52.803 --> 01:02:54.905
CAN I ASK YOU
A QUESTION?

01:02:54.905 --> 01:02:56.807
10 YEARS IN JAIL.

01:02:56.807 --> 01:02:57.908
WHAT?

01:02:57.908 --> 01:02:59.810
THE PENALTY
FOR "BORROWING" A BOAT

01:02:59.810 --> 01:03:01.411
THAT DOESN'T BELONG
TO YOU.

01:03:01.411 --> 01:03:02.813
IT'S CALLED PIRACY.

01:03:02.813 --> 01:03:04.214
10 YEARS IN JAIL.

01:03:04.214 --> 01:03:07.217
DO NOT PASS GO.
DO NOT COLLECT $200.

01:03:07.217 --> 01:03:10.420
YOU'RE RIGHT.
IT WAS A BAD IDEA.

01:03:10.420 --> 01:03:12.189
LET'S DO IT.

01:03:19.429 --> 01:03:20.530
JESSE?

01:03:20.530 --> 01:03:23.868
I'M DOWN IN DRAKE'S ROOM,
LOOKING FOR THE KEY.

01:03:27.771 --> 01:03:29.840
WHAT ARE YOU LOOKING FOR?

01:03:32.409 --> 01:03:34.644
THE SPARE STARTER KEY.

01:03:34.644 --> 01:03:36.046
YOU'RE STEALING
THE BOAT?

01:03:36.046 --> 01:03:37.314
AND GOING AFTER
THE WHALERS?

01:03:37.314 --> 01:03:38.315
YEAH.

01:03:38.315 --> 01:03:39.116
YOU'LL GO TO JAIL.

01:03:39.116 --> 01:03:40.584
I CAN LIVE WITH THAT.

01:03:40.584 --> 01:03:42.419
WHY?

01:03:42.419 --> 01:03:44.654
BECAUSE IT'S
THE RIGHT THING TO DO.

01:03:44.654 --> 01:03:46.256
YOU WORK FOR ME,
RANDOLPH.

01:03:46.256 --> 01:03:48.258
YOU UNDERSTAND THAT,
DON'T YOU?

01:03:48.258 --> 01:03:50.527
I GUESS YOU'LL
HAVE TO FIRE ME.

01:03:52.930 --> 01:03:54.965
WHAT IF...

01:03:54.965 --> 01:03:56.366
I WERE TO...

01:03:56.366 --> 01:04:00.270
ORDER YOU TO READY THIS BOAT
FOR IMMEDIATE DEPARTURE?

01:04:03.540 --> 01:04:05.542
IT MEANS
YOU LOSE YOUR JOB.

01:04:05.542 --> 01:04:08.812
HEY. THEY TOLD ME
TO KEEP AN EYE ON YOU,

01:04:08.812 --> 01:04:13.050
AND THAT IS EXACTLY
WHAT I'M GOING TO DO.

01:04:13.050 --> 01:04:16.286
* OH, NELLIE, NELLIE RAE *

01:04:16.286 --> 01:04:19.323
* THERE IS TROUBLE
ON THE WAY *

01:04:19.323 --> 01:04:24.294
* AS SHE ALWAYS
TREATS HER LOVERS ANYMORE *

01:04:24.294 --> 01:04:25.362
[LAUGHING]

01:04:28.332 --> 01:04:32.937
STEVENS, WHERE DID
YOU PUT THE BOAT?

01:04:40.510 --> 01:04:41.912
I DON'T HEAR ANYTHING.

01:04:41.912 --> 01:04:43.914
THE WHALES WILL.

01:04:43.914 --> 01:04:46.316
OK. THE SIGNAL
WE'VE STOLEN

01:04:46.316 --> 01:04:49.920
WILL TAKE OUT
THE WHOLE POD IN A WEEK.

01:04:49.920 --> 01:04:52.522
TELL SANDERSON
TO ARM THE HARPOON.

01:04:52.522 --> 01:04:53.924
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACH]

01:04:53.924 --> 01:04:55.559
[DOOR OPENS]

01:05:00.330 --> 01:05:01.731
HI, DAD.

01:05:01.731 --> 01:05:03.067
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

01:05:03.067 --> 01:05:05.869
I WAS LOOKING
FOR YOU.

01:05:05.869 --> 01:05:08.472
I GUESS
I FELL ASLEEP.

01:05:08.472 --> 01:05:10.374
WHAT'S GOING ON?

01:05:12.142 --> 01:05:13.743
Max:
I HAVE A QUESTION.

01:05:13.743 --> 01:05:15.145
HERE, MAX, TAKE THIS

01:05:15.145 --> 01:05:16.981
AND SQUEEZE SOME OIL DOWN
IN THE PIVOT JOINT THERE.

01:05:16.981 --> 01:05:19.984
WHY IS IT WRONG
TO HURT OTHER PEOPLE?

01:05:19.984 --> 01:05:21.585
THAT'S THE RULE, MAX.

01:05:21.585 --> 01:05:23.587
IT JUST IS.

01:05:23.587 --> 01:05:24.421
BUT...DON'T YOU

01:05:24.421 --> 01:05:25.990
EVER WANT TO DO
WHAT YOU WANT,

01:05:25.990 --> 01:05:27.992
NO MATTER
WHO IT HURTS?

01:05:27.992 --> 01:05:28.993
MAYBE.

01:05:28.993 --> 01:05:31.195
YOU JUST DON'T DO IT.

01:05:31.195 --> 01:05:32.729
WHY?

01:05:32.729 --> 01:05:33.730
WHY WHAT?

01:05:33.730 --> 01:05:36.000
WHY DON'T
YOU DO IT?

01:05:36.000 --> 01:05:37.867
PEOPLE HAVE RIGHTS.

01:05:37.867 --> 01:05:39.469
EVEN PEOPLE YOU HATE?

01:05:39.469 --> 01:05:40.270
YEP.

01:05:40.270 --> 01:05:42.139
I DIDN'T KNOW
I HAD RIGHTS.

01:05:42.139 --> 01:05:43.607
WELL, YOU DO.

01:05:43.607 --> 01:05:45.209
[SONAR PINGING]

01:05:57.221 --> 01:05:58.355
DAD.

01:05:58.355 --> 01:06:00.157
YES, MAX.

01:06:00.157 --> 01:06:03.627
WHAT IF WHALES
ARE LIKE PEOPLE?

01:06:03.627 --> 01:06:04.828
THEY AREN'T.

01:06:04.828 --> 01:06:07.031
BUT WHAT IF
THEY ARE?

01:06:07.031 --> 01:06:08.532
MAX, WHALES ARE ANIMALS.

01:06:08.532 --> 01:06:11.735
THEY WERE PUT HERE
BY GOD FOR US TO HUNT.

01:06:11.735 --> 01:06:12.869
YOU DON'T GET UPSET

01:06:12.869 --> 01:06:13.870
WHEN YOU EAT
A CHEESEBURGER, DO YOU?

01:06:13.870 --> 01:06:15.472
WHY NOT?

01:06:15.472 --> 01:06:17.274
WHALES DON'T FEEL.

01:06:17.274 --> 01:06:19.976
THEY AREN'T PEOPLE.

01:06:19.976 --> 01:06:21.711
THEY'RE JUST FISH.

01:06:21.711 --> 01:06:24.748
YOU'RE WRONG.

01:06:24.748 --> 01:06:26.750
YOU KNOW BETTER
THAN ME?

01:06:26.750 --> 01:06:28.185
YOU'RE 10 YEARS OLD.

01:06:28.185 --> 01:06:29.453
BUT YOU'RE WRONG, DAD.

01:06:29.453 --> 01:06:31.055
AND I'VE BEEN WRONG
ALL MY LIFE,

01:06:31.055 --> 01:06:32.956
AND MY DAD WAS WRONG,
AND HIS DAD, TOO?

01:06:32.956 --> 01:06:34.658
WE'RE ALL WRONG,
AND YOU'RE RIGHT.

01:06:34.658 --> 01:06:36.226
AND YOU'RE HURTING PEOPLE.

01:06:36.226 --> 01:06:39.429
WHO AM I HURTING?
I'M NOT HURTING ANYONE.

01:06:40.830 --> 01:06:42.132
CAPTAIN.

01:06:42.132 --> 01:06:43.600
WHAT IS IT THIS TIME?

01:06:43.600 --> 01:06:47.171
SORRY, CAPTAIN,
BUT I THINK YOU SHOULD KNOW.

01:06:47.171 --> 01:06:50.407
I FOUND THIS
IN THE ENGINE ROOM.

01:07:00.150 --> 01:07:02.619
[DOOR CLOSES AND LOCKS]

01:07:03.720 --> 01:07:05.222
"J" POD'S TURNING AROUND.

01:07:05.222 --> 01:07:08.425
THEY'RE HEADING RIGHT
FOR THE BOTANY BAY.

01:07:18.968 --> 01:07:20.570
WHERE ARE THEY?

01:07:20.570 --> 01:07:21.571
[WHALES CALLING]

01:07:21.571 --> 01:07:23.973
BY THE SOUND OF IT,

01:07:23.973 --> 01:07:26.643
ABOUT 5 KILOMETERS
NORTH-NORTHWEST.

01:07:26.643 --> 01:07:28.345
AND CLOSING.

01:07:28.345 --> 01:07:31.715
THIS THING
WORKS LIKE A CHARM.

01:07:31.715 --> 01:07:33.517
THEY'VE STOLEN YOUR SIGNAL.

01:07:33.517 --> 01:07:35.519
WILLY WON'T KNOW
THE DIFFERENCE.

01:07:35.519 --> 01:07:38.722
THEY'RE SWIMMING
RIGHT INTO A TRAP.

01:07:38.722 --> 01:07:40.490
THINKING IT'S ME.

01:07:52.602 --> 01:07:55.038
I CAN'T SEE A THING.

01:07:55.038 --> 01:07:57.274
Randolph:
WE'D BETTER HURRY.

01:07:58.142 --> 01:08:00.577
SOMETHING JUST
OCCURRED TO ME.

01:08:00.577 --> 01:08:01.645
YEAH?

01:08:01.645 --> 01:08:02.479
WHEN WE FIND THEM,

01:08:02.479 --> 01:08:04.681
WHAT ARE WE
GOING TO DO?

01:08:11.188 --> 01:08:13.357
THERE THEY ARE.

01:08:14.491 --> 01:08:15.659
10 O'CLOCK.

01:08:22.166 --> 01:08:24.334
LET'S GO.

01:08:33.243 --> 01:08:34.578
Randolph: WE'RE TOO LATE.

01:08:34.578 --> 01:08:36.513
NO. THEY'RE JUST AROUND
THE POINT.

01:08:36.513 --> 01:08:38.415
ALL WE NEED IS A FEW MINUTES
TO CATCH UP.

01:08:38.415 --> 01:08:39.849
WE DON'T HAVE
A FEW MINUTES.

01:08:41.417 --> 01:08:43.252
OK.

01:08:54.631 --> 01:08:56.233
HOLD HER STEADY.

01:09:05.008 --> 01:09:06.743
HEY, DAD!

01:09:06.743 --> 01:09:09.546
MAX, DON'T YOU DARE!

01:09:10.779 --> 01:09:12.816
MAN OVERBOARD!

01:09:12.816 --> 01:09:13.817
GO! GO, GO, GO, GO!

01:09:13.817 --> 01:09:14.818
HARD APORT!

01:09:14.818 --> 01:09:16.819
YES, SIR!

01:09:18.854 --> 01:09:20.823
NOW GO ASTERN!

01:09:20.823 --> 01:09:22.024
HARD ASTERN!

01:09:22.024 --> 01:09:23.426
RANDOLPH, LOOK AT THIS.

01:09:23.426 --> 01:09:25.028
BOTANY BAY
IS TURNING AROUND.

01:09:25.028 --> 01:09:26.296
THEY'RE DOING
A BIG CIRCLE.

01:09:26.296 --> 01:09:28.198
WHY WOULD THEY DO THAT?

01:09:29.131 --> 01:09:30.367
MAX.

01:09:31.835 --> 01:09:33.370
UHH!

01:09:33.370 --> 01:09:35.037
COME ON, MAX.

01:09:35.037 --> 01:09:36.171
GRAB THE RING.

01:09:36.171 --> 01:09:37.474
SAY YOU'RE WRONG!

01:09:37.474 --> 01:09:39.142
COME OUT
OF THE WATER NOW,

01:09:39.142 --> 01:09:41.176
OR YOU'LL
FREEZE TO DEATH.

01:09:41.176 --> 01:09:43.179
NO!

01:09:44.881 --> 01:09:46.015
GRAB IT, MAX!

01:09:46.015 --> 01:09:48.885
GRAB THE RING NOW!

01:10:04.033 --> 01:10:06.236
GET BELOW.

01:10:08.805 --> 01:10:09.806
LET'S GO.

01:10:09.806 --> 01:10:10.807
RIGHT.

01:10:13.310 --> 01:10:14.844
THERE SHE IS.

01:10:16.613 --> 01:10:18.948
BOTANY BAY,
THIS IS THE NOAH.

01:10:18.948 --> 01:10:20.417
WE KNOW WHO YOU ARE,

01:10:20.417 --> 01:10:21.585
AND WE KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE DOING.

01:10:21.585 --> 01:10:23.320
IF YOU ATTEMPT
TO HARM THESE WHALES...

01:10:23.320 --> 01:10:24.788
WHAT NOW?

01:10:24.788 --> 01:10:26.590
YOU'LL BE FIRED UPON.

01:10:26.590 --> 01:10:29.826
YOU WILL BE
FIRED UPON.

01:10:29.826 --> 01:10:30.927
WITH WHAT?

01:10:30.927 --> 01:10:32.462
WE DON'T HAVE ANYTHING
TO FIRE UPON THEM WITH.

01:10:32.462 --> 01:10:33.830
THEY DON'T KNOW THAT.

01:10:33.830 --> 01:10:34.898
RIGHT ON TOP OF THEM.

01:10:34.898 --> 01:10:37.100
I FIGURED THEY WOULD BE.
HERE, TAKE THE HELM.

01:10:37.100 --> 01:10:39.002
WHAT DO I DO?

01:10:39.002 --> 01:10:40.537
JUST STEER. IT'S EASY.

01:10:51.515 --> 01:10:53.049
READY THE SPEAR GUNS.

01:10:53.049 --> 01:10:54.284
RIGHT AWAY!

01:10:57.987 --> 01:11:00.457
NOAH, THIS IS
THE BOTANY BAY.

01:11:00.457 --> 01:11:02.526
WE'RE FISHING FOR SALMON.

01:11:02.526 --> 01:11:04.127
PLEASE STAY CLEAR OF US.

01:11:04.127 --> 01:11:05.995
WE CAN'T SEE A THING
IN THIS FOG.

01:11:13.537 --> 01:11:16.005
[ENGINES REVVING]

01:11:17.006 --> 01:11:18.342
COASTAL MARINE PATROL,

01:11:18.342 --> 01:11:20.410
THIS IS THE NOAH,
ON CHANNEL 16.

01:11:20.410 --> 01:11:21.411
MAYDAY. MAYDAY.

01:11:21.411 --> 01:11:23.012
THERE'S BEEN
A COLLISION.

01:11:23.012 --> 01:11:24.881
YOU BETTER LET ME STEER.

01:11:44.634 --> 01:11:47.771
AAH!

01:11:56.780 --> 01:11:58.515
[VOCALIZING]

01:12:12.462 --> 01:12:13.930
[VOCALIZING]

01:12:52.902 --> 01:12:54.037
NO.

01:12:54.037 --> 01:12:56.139
DAD!

01:12:56.139 --> 01:12:57.541
SHOOT IT NOW!

01:12:57.541 --> 01:12:59.443
FIRE!
WILLY, STOP!

01:13:00.510 --> 01:13:01.911
WILLY, NO!

01:13:03.513 --> 01:13:08.485
[SQUEAKING]

01:13:20.430 --> 01:13:22.966
[WILLY CRYING]

01:14:07.243 --> 01:14:09.479
[WILLY CRYING]

01:14:45.248 --> 01:14:47.383
OK.

01:14:47.383 --> 01:14:48.384
THERE.

01:14:48.384 --> 01:14:49.986
COME ON.

01:15:32.762 --> 01:15:36.132
[WILLY SINGING]

01:15:45.508 --> 01:15:47.310
HI.

01:15:47.310 --> 01:15:48.912
HI.

01:15:50.947 --> 01:15:55.084
A CHEESEBURGER
SAVED YOUR LIFE.

01:16:10.433 --> 01:16:12.135
YOU WERE RIGHT.

01:16:13.369 --> 01:16:15.371
HEY.

01:16:15.371 --> 01:16:18.007
YOU MADE A MISTAKE.

01:16:22.111 --> 01:16:24.113
WHAT AM I
SUPPOSED TO DO NOW?

01:16:24.113 --> 01:16:27.050
I'M A WHALER.
THAT'S WHAT I AM.

01:16:30.186 --> 01:16:31.587
NOT TO ME.

01:16:31.587 --> 01:16:33.690
YOU'RE MY DAD.

01:16:56.012 --> 01:16:58.614
IT'S NOT WHAT
I WOULD HAVE DONE.

01:16:58.614 --> 01:17:00.616
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

01:17:00.616 --> 01:17:03.019
I MEAN...SOME GUY
TRIES TO KILL ME,

01:17:03.019 --> 01:17:05.021
I WOULDN'T HAVE
SAVED HIS LIFE.

01:17:05.021 --> 01:17:06.756
I WOULD HAVE...
BIT HIS BUTT.

01:17:06.756 --> 01:17:08.825
WELL, MAYBE HE'S
SMARTER THAN WE ARE.

01:17:08.825 --> 01:17:10.226
OR MORE HUMAN.

01:17:11.861 --> 01:17:14.463
Jesse: WILLY'S GOING TO MAKE
A GOOD FATHER,

01:17:14.463 --> 01:17:15.865
DON'T YOU THINK?

01:17:15.865 --> 01:17:17.701
Randolph:
WHEN THE TIME COMES.

01:17:28.244 --> 01:17:29.645
Max: HEY, WILLY!

01:17:50.266 --> 01:17:52.969
[WILLY SINGING]

01:18:00.476 --> 01:18:02.846
[SINGING]

01:20:10.239 --> 01:20:12.909
[LAUGHING]

01:20:12.909 --> 01:20:14.143
I LIKE IT, DREW.

01:20:14.143 --> 01:20:15.711
IT BRINGS OUT YOUR EYES.

01:20:15.711 --> 01:20:18.014
WELL, ONE OF THEM,
AT LEAST.

01:20:18.982 --> 01:20:20.583
OH, YOU GUYS.

01:20:20.583 --> 01:20:21.885
JESSE, LOOK.

01:20:32.295 --> 01:20:34.497
WHAT ARE YOU
GOING TO NAME HIM?

01:20:34.497 --> 01:20:36.632
WHAT DO YOU SAY,
JESSE?

01:20:36.632 --> 01:20:39.035
I DON'T KNOW.

01:20:39.035 --> 01:20:40.469
WHAT DO YOU SAY?

01:20:40.469 --> 01:20:41.470
ME?

01:20:41.470 --> 01:20:42.471
YEAH.

01:20:44.640 --> 01:20:47.610
I SAY WE NAME HIM
AFTER HIS DAD.

01:20:49.112 --> 01:20:52.315
Jesse: WELL, I SAY
WE NAME HIM MAX.

